# Password Security Best Practices

**Your password is your first line of defense**

| Weak Password | Strong Password | Why It's Better |
|---------------|-----------------|-----------------|
| password123 | Tr@il$2024Run! | Length + complexity |
| john2024 | M0rning$C0ffee#9 | Unpredictable pattern |
| qwerty | B@sketb@ll#Finals | Special characters |

**Password Manager Recommended: All employees get free access**

::: info
**{{company}} Password Policy:**
- Minimum 12 characters
- Mix of letters, numbers, symbols
- Unique for each account
- Change if suspected compromise
:::

@notes:
- Demonstrate password strength checker
- Company provides password manager license
- Emphasize unique passwords for each account
- Password manager removes burden of memorization

---

