# Mobile Device Security

**Protecting company data on personal devices**

**Required Security Measures:**
- Screen lock with PIN/password/biometric
- Automatic lock after 5 minutes
- Regular OS and app updates
- Only download apps from official stores
- Report lost/stolen devices immediately

<<chart: radar>>
  data: [[9, 7, 8, 6, 9]]
  labels: ["Screen Lock", "OS Updates", "App Store Only", "Remote Wipe", "Data Encryption"]
  series: ["Security Effectiveness (1-10)"]
  options:
    responsive: true
    plugins:
      title:
        display: true
        text: "Mobile Security Controls Effectiveness"
    scales:
      r:
        beginAtZero: true
        max: 10

@notes:
- BYOD policy requires security measures
- Screen lock most important basic control
- Official app stores filter malicious apps
- Remote wipe capability for lost devices

---

# Safe Web Browsing

**Recognizing and avoiding malicious websites**

**Warning Signs of Malicious Sites:**
- No HTTPS lock icon in address bar
- Excessive pop-ups and ads
- Requests to download software
- Too-good-to-be-true offers
- Urgent warnings about computer problems

**Browser Security Tips:**
- Keep browsers updated
- Use reputable antivirus software
- Be cautious with downloads
- Verify SSL certificates for sensitive sites
- Use ad blockers on personal devices

@notes:
- HTTPS crucial for sensitive data
- Pop-ups often contain malware
- Fake security warnings common scam
- Browser updates include security patches

---

# Email Security Best Practices

**Protecting against email-based threats**

::: grid
::: column
**Before Opening Emails:**
- Verify sender identity
- Check for urgent language
- Examine links carefully
- Scan attachments
:::

::: column
**When Responding:**
- Use encryption for sensitive data
- BCC for large recipient lists
- Double-check recipients
- Keep company data internal
:::
:::

**Remember: Email is not private communication**

@notes:
- Verification prevents impersonation
- Urgent language creates pressure
- Encryption required for sensitive data
- BCC prevents email harvesting

---

# Compliance and Legal Requirements

**Meeting {{compliance_standard}} and regulatory standards**

**Your Role in Compliance:**
- Follow security policies consistently
- Complete required training annually
- Report security incidents promptly
- Maintain confidentiality of customer data
- Document security procedures

**Consequences of Non-Compliance:**
- Regulatory fines for the company
- Personal liability in some cases
- Damage to company reputation
- Loss of customer trust

@notes:
- Compliance is everyone's responsibility
- Annual training required for certification
- Customer data has special protection requirements
- Fines can be substantial for violations

